"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color-5","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color#multiple-series","content":"Multiple series"},"995":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color-6","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color#for-use-with-chart-components-not-exported","content":"Wrap your chart (or list) with `ChartColorProvider`; each component that calls `useChartColor()` receives a CSS variable reference. Indices are assigned in an effect at mount, so allocation is safe under React concurrent rendering and StrictMode. Same component instance keeps the same color; colors cycle after the ninth consumer. No need to pass an index—order in the tree determines assignment."},"996":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color-7","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color#single-series","content":"One series using the first chart color."},"997":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color-8","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color#multiple-series","content":"Multiple series each receiving the next color in sequence."},"998":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","type":"page","content":"useNormalizedSeries","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components","Chart"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series"},"999":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series-0","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","content":"A hook that ensures every series config has a stable unique id, generating one from useId when omitted."},"1000":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series-1","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series#for-use-with-chart-components-not-exported","content":"For use with chart components (not exported)"},"1001":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series-2","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series#for-use-with-chart-components-not-exported","content":"Accepts a `SeriesConfig[]` array and returns a memoized copy where each item is guaranteed to have an `id`. When an item has no `id`, one is generated using a component-scoped prefix from React's `useId`, ensuring IDs are unique across multiple chart instances on the same page. Existing `id` values are preserved as-is."},"1002":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","type":"page","content":"useScrollableXYChart","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components","Chart"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart"},"1003":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-0","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","content":"Layout hook for scrollable two-dimensional charts with X and Y axes—measures axis DOM and supplies margins, content-sized width and height, scroll offsets, and when category-axis ticks should read vertically."},"1004":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-1","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#for-use-with-chart-components-not-exported","content":"For use with chart components (not exported)"},"1005":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-2","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#purpose","content":"Purpose"},"1006":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-3","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#how-it-works","content":"How it works"},"1007":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-4","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#listeners-and-observers","content":"Listeners and observers"},"1008":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-5","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#how-to-implement","content":"How to implement"},"1009":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-6","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#props","content":"Props"},"1010":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-7","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#return-value--what-each-field-is-for","content":"Return value — what each field is for"},"1011":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-8","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#examples","content":"Examples"},"1012":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-9","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#auto-layout","content":"Auto layout"},"1013":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-10","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#purpose","content":"Built for **2D charts** with an **X axis** and a **Y axis** when the data plane can **overflow** inside a scroll container. Hard-coded `margin`, `width`, and `height` mis-size the SVG: ticks and labels need real space, and the value axis often stays visually fixed while the category axis scrolls. This hook **measures the axis DOM** you already render and returns **layout numbers** so the chart body, scales, and any frozen axis chrome stay consistent with what is on screen."},"1014":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-11","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#how-it-works","content":"**`useParentSize`** is bound to the scroll container (`parentRef`) to read the **visible** width and height of the plot slot."},"1015":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-12","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#how-it-works","content":"**`xAxisRef`*&#x2A; and &#x2A;*`yAxisRef`*&#x2A; point at the axis root groups. &#x2A;*`MutationObserver`*&#x2A; and &#x2A;*`ResizeObserver`** on those subtrees recompute **margins** (including overflow from tick labels), **minimum height** from stacked Y labels, and **minimum category-axis width** for horizontal vs vertical tick layouts."},"1016":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-13","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#how-it-works","content":"**`chartWidth`*&#x2A; and &#x2A;*`chartHeight`*&#x2A; combine the visible slot with those minima so the drawable area can grow past the viewport when labels require it. &#x2A;*`xLabelsVertical`*&#x2A; follows from &#x2A;*`xLabelsOrientation`** (see **Props**) and whether horizontal ticks would fit at the current width."},"1017":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-14","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#how-it-works","content":"Scroll and pointer handling on the scroll container are described below (**Listeners and observers*&#x2A;); they keep &#x2A;*`scrollLeft`*&#x2A; / &#x2A;*`scrollTop`** accurate and resync pointer-driven overlays after scroll."},"1018":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-15","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#listeners-and-observers","content":"**Scroll container** (the element that receives `parentRef`):"},"1019":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-16","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#listeners-and-observers","content":"**`ResizeObserver`*&#x2A; (via &#x2A;*`useParentSize`**, debounced) — tracks the container’s **client width and height** when the plot slot is resized."},"1020":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-17","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#listeners-and-observers","content":"**`scroll`*&#x2A; (passive listener) — updates &#x2A;*`scrollLeft`*&#x2A; / &#x2A;*`scrollTop`** and may dispatch a &#x2A;*synthetic `pointermove`** on the last pointer target so hit-testing stays aligned with the new scroll position."},"1021":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-18","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#listeners-and-observers","content":"**`pointermove`*&#x2A; (passive listener) — records &#x2A;*`clientX` / `clientY`*&#x2A; and &#x2A;*`event.target`** for that resync path."},"1022":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-19","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#listeners-and-observers","content":"**`pointerleave`** (passive listener) — clears the stored target when the pointer leaves the container so a stale element is not targeted after scroll."},"1023":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-20","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#listeners-and-observers","content":"**Y-axis root** (`yAxisRef`):"},"1024":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-21","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#listeners-and-observers","content":"**`MutationObserver`** (`childList`, `subtree`) — recomputes Y-driven **margin*&#x2A; and &#x2A;*`minHeight`** when tick/label DOM changes."},"1025":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-22","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#listeners-and-observers","content":"**`ResizeObserver`*&#x2A; — picks up layout/size changes on the axis group (e.g. font or tick density) and refreshes &#x2A;*`yAxisRect`**, **margins**, and related layout."},"1026":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-23","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#listeners-and-observers","content":"**X-axis root** (`xAxisRef`):"},"1027":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-24","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#listeners-and-observers","content":"**`MutationObserver`** (`childList`, `subtree`) — recomputes category-axis **min widths** (horizontal vs vertical tick modes) and related **margin** when tick/label DOM changes."},"1028":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-25","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#listeners-and-observers","content":"**`ResizeObserver`** — updates **bottom/right/left** margins from measured overflow on the X-axis subtree."},"1029":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-26","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#how-to-implement","content":"Call &#x2A;*`useScrollableXYChart()`*&#x2A; at the top of your chart component, or &#x2A;*`useScrollableXYChart({ xLabelsOrientation })`** when you need to override category-axis layout (see **Props**)."},"1030":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-27","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#how-to-implement","content":"Put &#x2A;*`parentRef`** on the DOM node that scrolls (the one with `overflow: auto` / `scroll` and the chart body inside it)."},"1031":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-28","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#how-to-implement","content":"Pass &#x2A;*`xAxisRef`*&#x2A; and &#x2A;*`yAxisRef`*&#x2A; to your X and Y axis components via whatever ref prop they expose (commonly &#x2A;*`innerRef`** on axis primitives)."},"1032":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-29","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#how-to-implement","content":"After mount, when &#x2A;*`chartWidth`*&#x2A; and &#x2A;*`chartHeight`*&#x2A; are positive, render the SVG (or chart wrapper) using those dimensions and &#x2A;*`margin`**."},"1033":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-30","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#how-to-implement","content":"Use &#x2A;*`xLabelsVertical`** to style category-axis labels (rotation, anchors, data attributes)."},"1034":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-31","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#how-to-implement","content":"Use &#x2A;*`scrollLeft`*&#x2A; / &#x2A;*`scrollTop`*&#x2A; (and optionally &#x2A;*`yAxisRect`**) to position frozen axis backgrounds and translated axis groups so they move with scroll while the plot content moves underneath."},"1035":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-32","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#props","content":"The hook accepts an optional **props** object as its first argument (`UseScrollableXYChartProps` in source). It is separate from the **return value** below."},"1036":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-33","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#props","content":"**`xLabelsOrientation`*&#x2A; — Category-axis label layout vs. container width. Values are the chart-level type &#x2A;*`XLabelsOrientation`*&#x2A;: &#x2A;*`'auto'`*&#x2A; (default), &#x2A;*`'horizontal'`*&#x2A;, or &#x2A;*`'vertical'`*&#x2A;. With &#x2A;*`'auto'`*&#x2A;, the hook chooses vertical labels when the visible width is too small for the measured horizontal-tick footprint (including Y-axis width). &#x2A;*`'horizontal'`*&#x2A; and &#x2A;*`'vertical'`*&#x2A; skip that width check and force the corresponding layout, which also feeds &#x2A;*`chartWidth`** minima via the horizontal vs vertical min-width paths."},"1037":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-34","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#return-value--what-each-field-is-for","content":"**`parentRef`** — Attach to the **scroll container*&#x2A;. Intention: anchor &#x2A;*`useParentSize`**, the **scroll** / **pointer*&#x2A; listeners, and &#x2A;*`ResizeObserver`** from that hook on the same node users scroll (see **Listeners and observers**)."},"1038":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-35","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#return-value--what-each-field-is-for","content":"**`xAxisRef` / `yAxisRef`** — Attach to the **axis root groups** (via `innerRef` or equivalent). Intention: give observers a stable subtree that matches rendered ticks and labels so margins and min sizes stay accurate."},"1039":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-36","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#return-value--what-each-field-is-for","content":"**`margin`** — `{ top, right, bottom, left }` in pixels, updated from measured axis geometry. Intention: pass straight into your chart’s margin model so the plot area clears tick overflow and axis thickness without hand tuning."},"1040":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-37","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#return-value--what-each-field-is-for","content":"**`chartWidth`** — Width in pixels, at least the visible container width and at least the width implied by category-axis labels (for the current vertical vs horizontal tick mode) plus Y-axis width. Intention: size the chart body so horizontal overflow scrolls instead of clipping ticks."},"1041":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-38","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#return-value--what-each-field-is-for","content":"**`minHeight`** — Minimum height implied by **Y-axis label stacking** (computed from label boxes and gaps). Intention: expose the **content-driven floor*&#x2A; separately when your layout or tests need it; &#x2A;*`chartHeight`** already applies this floor."},"1042":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-39","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#return-value--what-each-field-is-for","content":"**`chartHeight`** — Height in pixels, `max(visible height, minHeight)`. Intention: size the chart body so stacked Y labels always fit."},"1043":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-40","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#return-value--what-each-field-is-for","content":"**`xLabelsVertical`** — Boolean: category-axis ticks should read **vertically**. Intention: drive `tickLabelProps`, CSS, or `data-*` flags so narrow slots rotate labels without a separate breakpoint in the chart."},"1044":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-41","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#return-value--what-each-field-is-for","content":"**`scrollLeft` / `scrollTop`** — Current scroll offsets of the container. Intention: offset **sticky** axis layers (background rects, `transform`s) and any UI that must stay phase-locked with the scrolled data plane; also drives the hook’s post-scroll pointer resync."},"1045":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-42","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#return-value--what-each-field-is-for","content":"**`yAxisRect`** — `getBBox()` of the Y-axis group when available, else `null`. Intention: size or place **frozen Y-axis chrome** (e.g. a background band) aligned to the measured axis, independent of arbitrary margin guesses."},"1046":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-43","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#auto-layout","content":"Minimal scroll parent plus stub axis groups: same ref wiring and `data-*` surface the browser tests assert on."},"1047":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"page","content":"Box","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components","Layout"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box"},"1048":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-0","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box","content":"Polymorphic layout component providing consistent spacing, elevation, rounding, and self-alignment"},"1049":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-1","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box#installation","content":"Installation"},"1050":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-2","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box#props","content":"Props"},"1051":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-3","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box#scale-sizes","content":"Scale Sizes"},"1052":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-4","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box#examples","content":"Examples"},"1053":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-5","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box#padding","content":"Padding"},"1054":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-6","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box#elevation","content":"Elevation"},"1055":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-7","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box#rounding","content":"Rounding"},"1056":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-8","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box#polymorphic-as-prop","content":"Polymorphic `as` Prop"},"1057":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-9","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box#alignment","content":"Alignment"},"1058":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-10","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box#rtl-support","content":"RTL Support"},"1059":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-11","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box#design-tokens","content":"Design Tokens"},"1060":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-12","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box","content":"Box is a polymorphic layout component that renders as any HTML element or custom component via the `as` prop. It provides consistent spacing, elevation, rounding, and self-alignment within flex or grid containers."},"1061":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-13","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box","content":"**Important**: Since `Flex` and `Grid` extend `Box`, prefer them for layouts. Use `Box` only when you need a non-flex, non-grid container."},"1062":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-14","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#props","content":"The `Box` component accepts the following props:"},"1063":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-15","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#scale-sizes","content":"The spacing props use semantic t-shirt sizes for padding, gap, and other spacing properties:"},"1064":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-16","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#scale-sizes","content":"`xs` - Extra small spacing"},"1065":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-17","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#scale-sizes","content":"`sm` - Small spacing"},"1066":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-18","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#scale-sizes","content":"`md` - Medium spacing"},"1067":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-19","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#scale-sizes","content":"`lg` - Large spacing"},"1068":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-20","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#scale-sizes","content":"`xl` - Extra large spacing"},"1069":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-21","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#scale-sizes","content":"`2xl` - 2x extra large spacing"},"1070":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-22","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#scale-sizes","content":"Custom CSS values are also supported for edge cases."},"1071":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-23","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#padding","content":"The padding props support t-shirt sizes and CSS logical properties for RTL support."},"1072":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-24","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#elevation","content":"The elevation prop adds visual depth using box-shadow."},"1073":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-25","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#rounding","content":"The rounding prop sets border-radius. Use `full` for fully rounded corners."},"1074":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-26","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#polymorphic-as-prop","content":"Box is fully polymorphic - the `as` prop allows rendering as any HTML element or custom component while preserving type-safe props."},"1075":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-27","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#polymorphic-as-prop","content":"**HTML Elements:** When using `as=\"button\"`, TypeScript enforces button-specific props like `type`, `disabled`, and `onClick`."},"1076":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-28","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#polymorphic-as-prop","content":"**Custom Components:** When using `as={MyComponent}`, Box accepts that component's props. If there's a prop name conflict, Box's props take priority."},"1077":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-29","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#polymorphic-as-prop","content":"**Typed Refs:** Refs are correctly typed based on the `as` value - `useRef<HTMLButtonElement>` works with `as=\"button\"`."},"1078":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-30","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#alignment","content":"Self-alignment props allow Box to position itself within flex or grid containers."},"1079":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-31","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#rtl-support","content":"Box uses CSS logical properties (`padding-inline-start`, `padding-block-end`, etc.) which automatically adapt to RTL layouts. No additional configuration is needed."},"1080":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-32","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#design-tokens","content":"All spacing, elevation, and rounding values are derived from the theme. If no theme is provided, default values are used. This ensures consistency across the design system."},"1081":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/flex","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/flex","type":"page","content":"Flex","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components","Layout"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/flex"},"1082":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/flex-0","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/flex","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/flex","content":"One-dimensional layout component for arranging children in rows or columns with alignment and spacing control"},"1083":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/flex-1","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/flex","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/flex#installation","content":"Installation"},"1084":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/flex-2","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/flex","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/flex#props","content":"Props"},"1085":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/flex-3","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/flex","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/flex#scale-sizes","content":"Scale Sizes"},"1086":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/flex-4","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/flex","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/flex#examples","content":"Examples"},"1087":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/fle