144":1067,"1145":312,"1146":634,"1147":1075,"1148":864,"1149":907,"1150":590,"1151":1051,"1152":629,"1153":784,"1154":630,"1155":368,"1156":632,"1157":786,"1158":591,"1159":615,"1160":631},"orderedDocs":[[1042,"**`chartHeight`** — Height in pixels, `max(visible height, minHeight)`. Intention: size the chart body so stacked Y labels always fit."],[1040,"**`chartWidth`** — Width in pixels, at least the visible container width and at least the width implied by category-axis labels (for the current vertical vs horizontal tick mode) plus Y-axis width. Intention: size the chart body so horizontal overflow scrolls instead of clipping ticks."],[1016,"**`chartWidth`*&#x2A; and &#x2A;*`chartHeight`*&#x2A; combine the visible slot with those minima so the drawable area can grow past the viewport when labels require it. &#x2A;*`xLabelsVertical`*&#x2A; follows from &#x2A;*`xLabelsOrientation`** (see **Props**) and whether horizontal ticks would fit at the current width."],[230,"**`icon.content`**: Overrides the BentoIllustration component - affects SVG transformations (rotate, flip), accessibility attributes (`role`, `focusable`, `aria-labelledby`), viewBox calculations, and final SVG element rendering"],[229,"**`icon`**: Overrides the entire BentoIcon component - affects icon loading, caching, sprite/SVG mode switching, data attributes, and the overall icon wrapper"],[1039,"**`margin`** — `{ top, right, bottom, left }` in pixels, updated from measured axis geometry. Intention: pass straight into your chart’s margin model so the plot area clears tick overflow and axis thickness without hand tuning."],[1041,"**`minHeight`** — Minimum height implied by **Y-axis label stacking** (computed from label boxes and gaps). Intention: expose the **content-driven floor*&#x2A; separately when your layout or tests need it; &#x2A;*`chartHeight`** already applies this floor."],[1027,"**`MutationObserver`** (`childList`, `subtree`) — recomputes category-axis **min widths** (horizontal vs vertical tick modes) and related **margin** when tick/label DOM changes."],[1024,"**`MutationObserver`** (`childList`, `subtree`) — recomputes Y-driven **margin*&#x2A; and &#x2A;*`minHeight`** when tick/label DOM changes."],[237,"**`ondemand(loader)`**: Register an asynchronous icon loader (returns unregister function)"],[1037,"**`parentRef`** — Attach to the **scroll container*&#x2A;. Intention: anchor &#x2A;*`useParentSize`**, the **scroll** / **pointer*&#x2A; listeners, and &#x2A;*`ResizeObserver`** from that hook on the same node users scroll (see **Listeners and observers**)."],[238,"**`parser(svgString)`**: Parse SVG strings into React elements"],[1022,"**`pointerleave`** (passive listener) — clears the stored target when the pointer leaves the container so a stale element is not targeted after scroll."],[1021,"**`pointermove`*&#x2A; (passive listener) — records &#x2A;*`clientX` / `clientY`*&#x2A; and &#x2A;*`event.target`** for that resync path."],[1028,"**`ResizeObserver`** — updates **bottom/right/left** margins from measured overflow on the X-axis subtree."],[1025,"**`ResizeObserver`*&#x2A; — picks up layout/size changes on the axis group (e.g. font or tick density) and refreshes &#x2A;*`yAxisRect`**, **margins**, and related layout."],[1019,"**`ResizeObserver`*&#x2A; (via &#x2A;*`useParentSize`**, debounced) — tracks the container’s **client width and height** when the plot slot is resized."],[1020,"**`scroll`*&#x2A; (passive listener) — updates &#x2A;*`scrollLeft`*&#x2A; / &#x2A;*`scrollTop`** and may dispatch a &#x2A;*synthetic `pointermove`** on the last pointer target so hit-testing stays aligned with the new scroll position."],[1044,"**`scrollLeft` / `scrollTop`** — Current scroll offsets of the container. Intention: offset **sticky** axis layers (background rects, `transform`s) and any UI that must stay phase-locked with the scrolled data plane; also drives the hook’s post-scroll pointer resync."],[236,"**`set(icons)`**: Synchronously add icons to the store"],[1014,"**`useParentSize`** is bound to the scroll container (`parentRef`) to read the **visible** width and height of the plot slot."],[1038,"**`xAxisRef` / `yAxisRef`** — Attach to the **axis root groups** (via `innerRef` or equivalent). Intention: give observers a stable subtree that matches rendered ticks and labels so margins and min sizes stay accurate."],[1015,"**`xAxisRef`*&#x2A; and &#x2A;*`yAxisRef`*&#x2A; point at the axis root groups. &#x2A;*`MutationObserver`*&#x2A; and &#x2A;*`ResizeObserver`** on those subtrees recompute **margins** (including overflow from tick labels), **minimum height** from stacked Y labels, and **minimum category-axis width** for horizontal vs vertical tick layouts."],[1036,"**`xLabelsOrientation`*&#x2A; — Category-axis label layout vs. container width. Values are the chart-level type &#x2A;*`XLabelsOrientation`*&#x2A;: &#x2A;*`'auto'`*&#x2A; (default), &#x2A;*`'horizontal'`*&#x2A;, or &#x2A;*`'vertical'`*&#x2A;. With &#x2A;*`'auto'`*&#x2A;, the hook chooses vertical labels when the visible width is too small for the measured horizontal-tick footprint (including Y-axis width). &#x2A;*`'horizontal'`*&#x2A; and &#x2A;*`'vertical'`*&#x2A; skip that width check and force the corresponding layout, which also feeds &#x2A;*`chartWidth`** minima via the horizontal vs vertical min-width paths."],[1043,"**`xLabelsVertical`** — Boolean: category-axis ticks should read **vertically**. Intention: drive `tickLabelProps`, CSS, or `data-*` flags so narrow slots rotate labels without a separate breakpoint in the chart."],[1045,"**`yAxisRect`** — `getBBox()` of the Y-axis group when available, else `null`. Intention: size or place **frozen Y-axis chrome** (e.g. a background band) aligned to the measured axis, independent of arbitrary margin guesses."],[217,"**Accessibility ready**: Built-in support for screen readers and keyboard navigation"],[713,"**Accessibility ready**: Keyboard navigation, screen reader support, and semantic HTML"],[222,"**